name: Gmail AttachmentIcons - NtmVersion
description:
ATTENTION!!!
This Script is OUTDATED and discontinued!!!
==================================================

Another Gmail Attachment Icons style!

- This style use the system icons, so i do not provide any screens.
- It puts icons in inbox zone, inside mail and some in the new attachments zone!
- Supports 142 extensions types and 10 'gType' formats.

note: If you want some specific extension or 'gType' that is not present in this script please say something in the discussions. I will, probably, include your request in my next update!
ps: I may do this script from scratch again but I don't promise anything.
additional_info:
########## (v2.000) ##########
- Re-write the style from scratch.
- Optimization to make the size of the style as small as possible, but at a bare minimum readable state.
- Icons inside mail again since the Google update broken the old code.
- New extension types, 23 to be more exact.
- Some 'gType' use local icons, 10 to be precise, is the new attachments zone.

########## (v1.510) ##########
- Style renamed.

########## (v1.500) ##########
- Icons inside mail in addition to only in the inbox zone.
- Discovered 2 duplicated extensions, new total, 119.

########## (v1.210) ##########
- More extensions, 121 in total.

########## (v1.200) ##########
- A complete makeover from scratch, much better compatibility now.
- Many more extensions, 114 in total.

########## (v0.940) ##########
- 1st public release.

--------------------------------------------------
Some notes and infos you may like to know...
Actually the 'gType' formats are the attachments zone and I'm aware of 14 different format types that Google use/name.
In this next list are the ones I make a choice to use an icon:...
- "Android Package"   ------> apk
- "Excel"   ----------------> xls
- "PDF"   ------------------> pdf
- "PowerPoint"   -----------> ppt
- "Rich Text"   ------------> rtf
- "Text"   -----------------> txt
- "vCard"   ----------------> vcf
- "Windows Media Player"   -> wmv
- "Word"   -----------------> doc
- "XML"   ------------------> xml
...and this next one I chose not to:...
"Compressed Archive"
"Google Docs"
"Image"
"Video"
...I don't use any icon on those because they serve too many different extensions types and that may be a bit misleading, eg: in "Image" a PNG, JPG, GIF, and more will all present the same icon; or they serve a very specific type like the "Google Docs" that probably there isn't a local icon for.
